import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['open'].plot(kind='hist', bins=20, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['open'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean = {data['open'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['open'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median = {data['open'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title("What is the distribution of 'open' prices?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
